Class AbstractDetectPresenceAttribute

  • java.lang.Object
    • extractor.InformationUnit
      • extractor.AbstractDetectPresenceAttribute
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<InformationUnit>

    public class AbstractDetectPresenceAttribute
extends InformationUnit
    This class defines the functionalities required to extract the BCTs, which are of 'detect presence' type, i.e. one needs to predict if a given BCT applies for a research study or not.
    Author:
    dganguly

      • construct

        public void construct(String window,
                      org.apache.lucene.search.Query q,
                      float sim)
        The purpose of this function is to make sure that the flow for the DP attributes is consistent with the VE ones. For the DP type attributes, there's no particular candidate answer for which scores need to be aggregated. Instead, the whole retrieved passage is a candidate answer. The job of the overrideen function is hence to set bestAnswer correctly for consistent aggregation.
        Overrides:
        construct in class InformationUnit
        Parameters:
        window - A supplied text snippet.
        q - A query pertaining to a BCT attribute.
        sim - Similarity threshold that is used to decide the presence/absence of a BCT.
